race.comment: It's D-Day for TARPAULIN (2) who hasn't fired this time in having promised plenty as a younger horse. The drop back to 955m at Moonee Valley last time brought him unstuck, not the first horse to struggle at that specialist distance. Midfield in a far stronger race at Flemington prior has him the one to beat. EDGES DIAMOND (4) is the one with upside, winning narrowly first up at Geelong before folding late as a $3.20 chance at Bendigo. Can bounce back quickly. BINE (3) struggled in a strong BM70 at Moonee Valley last time behind some very speedy types. The fresh run behind Trembles is good form for this. THE WIZARD KING (6) is going okay and can figure on an each way basis while FLUX (7) was better last time and has minor claims.
